The paper introduces a new optimization problem for learning tasks on graphs and hypergraphs, which suggests it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The problem involves submodular functions, which are often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses numerical experiments, which could indicate a focus on computational methods and optimization (cs.SI).
